          <msContents>
            <summary>Contains a full version of the Bhāgavatapurāṇa, second skandha, which claims to be the answer to all questions, contains a description of avatāras of the Hindu god Kṛṣṇa, the process of creation, and portrays Kṛṣṇa (Vāsudeva) as the cause of the universe; it is a companion to Śrīdharasvamin's commentary, the Bhāgavatabhāvārthadīpikā, contained in Item 2306.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Bhāgavatamahāpurāṇa.</title>
              <title type="vernacular">भागवतमहापुराण</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrībhāgavate mahāpurāṇe aṣṭā daśasāhasyāṃ saṃhitāyāṃ dvitīyaskaṃdhe daśamodhyāyaḥ // samāpto 'yaṃ dvitīyaskaṃdhaḥ (f. 16v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
